Servings: 6

INGREDIENTS:
3 pounds Granny Smith apples
2 tbsp lemon juice
1/2 cup sugar
1/2 tsp cinammon
1/2 tsp nutmeg
1/2 cup flour
1/2 cup brown sugar
1/2 cup rolled oats (uncooked oatmeal)
1/2 stick cold butter
1/2 cup chopped walnuts or pecans

DIRECTIONS:
1.  Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
2.  Butter a 10 x 10 inch baking dish.
3.  Peel, core, and chop or slice the apples.  Put the apples in a bowl.
4.  Toss the apples with the lemon juice.
5.  In a different bowl, combine the sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg.  Stir this mix into the apples.  Set aside.
6.  In a separate bowl combine the flour, brown sugar, and rolled oats.  Cut the butter into this mixture until it looks like crumbs.
7.  Add the nuts to the flour mixture and stir.
8.  Spread the apples into the bottom of the baking dish.  
9.  Sprinkle the flour mixture on top of the apples.
10.  Bake for 45 minutes or until the topping is lightly browned.
11.  Serve warm or at room temperature with vanilla ice cream.
